You stand before a medium sized tree, with its leaves
blowing in the wind. It has a pleasant smell and seems
to be healthy. Nothing interesting here.
You see another dead animal remains that have some
of the similar blue dust you saw on the previous animal.
You approach a skeleton of a dead deer swarming with
flies. You immediately smell a terrible stench that
makes your nostrels flare. What would you like to do?
The skeleton has seen its fair share of wear and tear,
and it is almost picked clean. Scavangers and flies
have mainly picked it clean, but you are able to see
a strange blue dust on some of the bones.
